  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and multifaceted, designed to combat the concealment and disguising of illicitly obtained funds to make them appear legitimate. It involves international treaties, national laws, and regulatory bodies. Here's a breakdown:\n\n**I. International Framework:**\n\n*   **Financial Action Task Force (FATF):**  The global standard-setter.\n    *   Develops international standards (the \"Forty Recommendations\") to combat money laundering, terrorist financing, and proliferation financing.\n    *   Conducts mutual evaluations of member countries to assess their compliance with the standards.\n    *   Identifies high-risk and non-cooperative jurisdictions and provides guidance on dealing with them.  FATF Recommendations are not legally binding themselves, but they are",
